Might be a bit too out there, but apparently Dr. Gerald Pollack says that even though glucose increases structured EZ-water in lab experiments, salt actually reduces the amount of EZ-water. This mirrors how Kozyrev said sugar and salt have opposite effects on the flow of time.

This has to do with depolarization and hyperpolarization of cells and the action potential thing and has to do with the "energized = resting" idea. Kozyrev held that sugar slows down time and salt speeds it up, I guess it would somehow be analogous even though it sounds so crazy.

The EZ-water being reduced by salt thing makes sense because salt is supposed to be outside the cell and the EZ is inside the cell where you need the structure, you would want extracellular salt to take the bulk water outside of the cell.

This is why sugar and salt are so complementary and e.g. both help with restful sleep or can take you out of shock in IV. Salt lowers adrenalin and allows efficient use of sugar, sugar's anti-stress effects help not lose salt, etc. Salted caramel was genius Soylennial invention.

This is actually a good example on how in the real (including paranormal) world everything works through "fields". Like how oxidation creates a formative field in the organism. The living equivalent to warping the mailbox would be causing cancer. Organization vs. disorganization.

One more thing about Survivorman is any time there is a goofy/funny sound effect over footage of Les Stroud doing jumping jacks to warm himself or going naked around a fire to dry off, it means he lost an argument with the TV guys. His vision is cold and pure. No any zany noises.

Like he will make little jokes in front of the camera and be funny and joke around, but demands no wacky edits or sound effects in the studio. This is raw wilderness survival. People die out there. All humor unfolds in the shadow of death. Editing must reflect nature's neutrality
